View Now: Miami 📍 AZULIN is live at Hologram: The Whole Story curated by @rvancelette shown at @thewallartgallery 

AZULIN was inspired by the Mangroves in Central America. The piece’s color is not the classic of the mangrove but represents its environment. These shrubs have a thirst for saltwater, as they have no home without it. They are connected to the sea, rooted in it. The piece aims to encapsulate the viewer with its twists and turns and lure them into exploring further, like the mangrove tempts to do with the dense wall of its branches.

50 NW 27th Street Miami, Florida

Up close 👀: AZULIN is live at Hologram: The Whole Story, curated by @rvancelette at the @thewallartgallery 

AZULIN was inspired by the shape of the mangroves—a dense and interlaced tree. Nature is the purest form and most source of beauty; the mangrove is no exception, with its bright green leaves and deep roots lacing one another. Mangroves are a natural filter for the environment, protecting water quality by removing nutrients and pollutants. They protect those surrounding them by absorbing the influx of water due to heavy rains and storm surges. Mangroves are nature’s protectors, and those living there interact with them.

Illuminating now 💙: AZULIN is live at Hologram: The Whole Story, curated by @rvancelette shown at @thewallartgallery

NOUR RIYADH FESTIVAL - AMPLEXUS 

This piece takes inspiration from traditional Islamic architecture, reinterpreting it within a digital age. At the same time, it engages with the modern shape of the installation site, @saudidq , the heart of the city’s global relations. The light sculpture was installed into a distinctive circular form that overhangs from building. The lighting sequence reconnects the city with the surrounding desert by recalling sunrises and sunsets on dunes. Tubing structures formed with the columns of the building and reflective material installed on the floor below will envelop viewers within their cultural heritage, community, and environment.

Thousands of souls dreaming and working together created the city of Riyadh. The breathtaking ferocity of the surrounding desert is a testament to human innovation. 

AMPLEXUS embraces this collective community consciousness, the city’s architecture, and the untamed magic of the desert itself.

SCIENTIA

The Latin word for knowledge. The word implies a socially interactive activity; the seeking and sharing of wisdom. This artwork explores the human connection using our elemental understanding of the world—fire, water, earth, and light. Because of this primordial immersion, SCIENTIA provides a means of accessing our emotional selves. Thus, the work nurtures wellbeing and promotes community engagement.

Description: LED light tubes interact with the Atrium of Cultures by twisting around the pillars in the room. Therefore, the light sculpture engages viewers in a dialogue with the architecture.

📍: @azkunazentroa w/ @thewellbeingp

SCIENTIA

“In order to create large-scale sculptures, I require an understanding of how our environment affects our state of mind. My site-specific light sculpture SCIENTIA engages visitors in a dialogue with architecture and community. Therefore, the work encourages moments of realization while creating connection through the medium of light.”

📍AZKUNA ZENTROA

SCIENTIA

The sequence was inspired by breathing. A breathe can represent a moment, a time to take a second to ourselves; reminding us we are alive and present. To balance ourselves we must first take a moment to remember the importance of caring for the self, for our being. #Mentalhealthawareness is the first step to taking care of the body and mind you have for life.

GRIMANESA X MERCADO GLOBAL 

Had a wonderful time with the Mercado Global community discussing my works and the importance of women supporting women. 

Mercado Global’s mission is to transform the lives of Indigenous women through fashion. All their products are handmade and are expertly crafted using traditional weaving techniques that play a crucial part in slowing down the fashion industry. With every purchase, you’re supporting the preservation of ancient knowledge passed from generation to generation for centuries.

GRIMANESA X MERCADO GLOBAL

It means so much to gather strong women in one place, to support each others successes. I loved sharing my experience as a woman light artist with everyone and showing no idea is to big or to small ✨

Mercado Global provides women from Indigenous communities the education and space transform their lives through fashion. All their products are handmade and are expertly crafted using traditional weaving techniques that play a crucial part in slowing down the fashion industry and giving these women new advantages.

“No Longer Empty: Building Art and Community in Unused Spaces” by @manon_slome is now on Amazon!

Check out my piece TAPIZ which was commissioned by @nolongerempty , as the cover of Manon’s book. Her book highlights and reflects on New York City’s public artwork and touches upon the development of a curatorial program that aimed to create democratic access to art through site-and community responsive exhibitions and radical educational programming grounded by research. 

Grab your copy ✨

OUT NOW: TAPIZ on the cover of @manon_slome book, “No Longer Empty: Building Art and Community in Unused Spaces.” 

The book traces the evolution of the group’s highly innovative curatorial, educational and collaborative programmatic strategies. Case studies of selected exhibitions, short accounts by a host of artists and educators, and replicas of forms and checklists function as a kind of manual to inspire the next generations of makers and agents of change—curators, artists, community organizers, educators—who want to take cultural production and the power of art into their own hands and into their own communities.

✨ Now on Amazon ✨

OUT NOW: TAPIZ as the cover of “No Longer Empty: Building Art and Community in Unused Spaces” by @manon_slome 

TAPIZ was conceived as a floating map representing the richness and ethnic diversity of the neighborhood in East Harlem. Gleaming and visible from afar, the corner window installation worked to dissolve boundaries between the exhibition and the life beyond it through complex overlapping portraits of people living in the community.

BEHIND THE SCENES: A PIECE COMES TO LIFE

Media: LEDs, diffusion and reflective material, custom lighting sequence, electrical hardware, stainless steel.
Dimensions: 9 ft x 5 ft 4 in x 5 ft 4 in

This piece is comprised of two main sections. The left side is based on the island Manhattan, while the right represents the Bronx. New York started in lower Manhattan and expanded all the way to the Bronx. These two boroughs represent the limits of the city and the development of the future.

Media: LEDs, diffusion and reflective material, custom lighting sequence, electrical hardware, stainless steel.
Dimensions: 9 ft x 5 ft 4 in x 5 ft 4 in

ABOUT

The piece is comprised of two main sections. The left side is based on the island Manhattan, while the right represents the Bronx. New York started in lower Manhattan and expanded all the way to the Bronx. These two boroughs represent the limits of the city and the development of the future.

The relationship between the pieces location, 80 White Street’s steel foundation and AIM’s new future in Manhattan inspired me to combine two vital parts of the building; it’s foundation and residents. I decided to use stainless steel, but not the conventional reflective one. The stainless steel that’s being used is mirrored, but not as much to where the viewer can see their perfect reflection. The image one sees is blurred and slightly skewed, making it seem almost like silver. As the piece occupies most of the entrance, the viewer is constantly interacting with it. When entering and exiting the building, the observer sees themselves, but much like light’s speed, it can never be fully captured and only appreciated in movement.

As many of you know, I live on a plane. Being up in the sky enables me to have personal time for reflection and understanding. Looking out to these golden clouds made me think about how world has been going (goes) through hurt and hardship, I wanted to shed some light on the parts that are beautiful like the #nature we live in. It has always been a source of inspiration for myself and art, from the coca leaves to mangroves to the waves of the ocean and the sky. The environment wow’s me every day. You never know what every day brings you, so I always say, “I live in a constant romance with the unknown.” ✨❤️ Let the unknown speak to you; you never know what you’ll hear back 🤗

As seen in NY Magazine;

PARADISUS: is defined in Latin as paradise or park. After visiting Japan many years ago, my appreciation and recognition of natural elements grew deeper.

I was then reminded of my childhood when I spent countless hours exploring my mother's garden, which felt like the most serene place.

The Ritsurin Garden is located in Takamatsu, Japan. In this garden lays the azalea flowering shrubs. Many are unknown about the azalea's potency and toxicity. It is beautiful but dangerous. The combination of beauty and pain is a known concept; the juxtaposition of something so delicate can be remarkably resilient and potent is what inclined the creation of PARADISUS, a fictional place or, to some, believed to exist.

AUREUM: is the first in a series of pieces where I use light metaphorically to inspire creativity and clarity for the viewer. The golden lighting sequence is continuously changing. When the viewer enters and exits the space, they are given a different experience each time. AUREUM will create an area where the viewer can leave the outside elements and envelop themselves in an environment of wonderment and light.

dm @leilahellergallery or email ella@leilaheller.com for PARADISUS & AUREUM

LUMINOUS PORTRAITS:

Grimanesa Amoros masterfully combines vibrant colors, geometric designs inspired by Pre Columbian textiles and ceramics, and sleek metallic textures to create a captivating visual language that unites past and present. This fusion reflects the relationship between Incan sun ceremonies and a futurist aesthetic, both driven by a shared fascination with vitality, life, and technological progress.

Immerse yourself in Amoros’ dynamic approach that embraces her Peruvian cultural roots while embracing groundbreaking innovations. The LUMINOUS PORTRAITS series prompts us to contemplate how tradition shapes our collective future. Discover the transformative power of heritage and new possibilities in this remarkable collection.

About the work: Unveiling the mystical tapestry of my artistic journey, inspired by my beloved Peruvian heritage. 🌿✨ Growing up in Peru, I was enchanted by the profound ancient spirituality that permeates our land, embracing indigenous traditions and rituals passed down through generations. It was within this sacred context that I discovered the mesmerizing allure of the Tiwanaku culture and its sacred body markings, which held deep spiritual significance.

In my art, I pay homage to these ancient spiritual practices, infusing each creation with reverence and mysticism. I strive to be a bridge between the ancient and the contemporary, inviting viewers to embark on a timeless voyage into the realm of spirituality and connect with their own inner journey.

With each brushstroke and sculptural form, I aim to awaken the spirit and unlock the doors of perception. My art becomes a vessel, carrying the ancient wisdom and captivating energy of Tiwanaku into the present, inspiring contemplation and introspection.

My artwork illuminates the way, bridging the gap between past and present, tradition and innovation. Let us embark together on a profound exploration of spirituality, connecting with our inner selves and discovering the infinite possibilities that lie within. 🌌✨

Growing up in peru I used to sit here in this very spot and look out into the horizon wondering what the other side of the sky held for me. Behind the crashing waves of costal Lima lays the sliver of horizon. It’s this curiosity for the beyond that led me to my venture to New York and the life I lead now. Our roots create who we are, and I am grateful these crashing waves and continuous horizon created the foundation of my journey beyond my borders.

🌟 Introducing FLEXUS✨ It’s in its early stages, coming to life. You’ll come along with me on the journey 🤗. 🏙️ FLEXUS is an immersive experience where art and urban landscapes collide in a symphony of light and color. FLEXUS will illuminate the NYC skyline. 🌆✨ Stay tuned 🗽💫

🔸 Discover FLEXUS, where art and architecture intertwine.🔸

Growing up, my father would take me to his construction sites, where he allowed me to roam. Through this, I learned about the significance of roads and how they unite distant places and serve as conduits of human connection. These memories fueled my imagination and kindled a deep appreciation for the hidden allure of our transport networks. Through FLEXUS, I strive to share this experience with you, inviting you to perceive roads not merely as utilitarian pathways but as poetic expressions of our shared human experience.

✨ With synchronized lighting sequences and a commitment to sustainability, FLEXUS invites you to reimagine aesthetics. This piece uses energy-efficient lighting technologies and conscious design choices, conjoining art and ecological consciousness. ✨🌱

Day✌🏼of #AETERNUM 

🔜 Reveal 😄

AETERNUM 🌌✨ Delve into the eternal dance of sun and moon as Amoros pays tribute to the ancient lunisolar calendar—a meditation on everlasting existence, perpetual motion, and the unceasing flame of eternity. Witness the narrative of commissioners intertwined like twin flames, encapsulated within the hourglass, where sands of change flow relentlessly. Embracing infinite possibilities, AETERNUM breaks the illusion of endings and invites you to ponder time’s intricate threads in the fabric of our human journey. 🕰️🔥

#AETERNUM shines in its hourglass form. The “sands” of time steadily trickle down, representing the inevitable nature of change. Inspired by the moment the hourglass is reset, the illusion breaks of conclusive endings and embraces the infinite possibilities. This piece is an immersive light sculpture seamlessly intertwining the commissioner’s essence with my artistic vision.

Keep an eye out for an upcoming conversation between me and @angelicasem, where we delve deeper into the heart of this project. ✨

🌟 AETERNUM: Captivating the Essence of Time 🕰️ |
Year: 2023 | Dimensions: 4.2 ft x 4.2 ft x 16 ft | Media: LEDs, diffusion material, custom lighting sequence, electrical hardware

Introducing AETERNUM: an exploration that unravels the intricate dance between time, change, and eternity. Immerse yourself in a thought-provoking journey through the vast tapestry of human experience. This sculpture draws inspiration from the pivotal moment an hourglass resets, shattering the illusion of finality and embracing boundless possibilities.

Commissioned by Ellipsis Fine Art Advisory @angelicasem 

Discover the fascinating interplay of light at http://www.grimanesaamoros.com. ✨

And some art commission projects are simply a dream to work on - combining creative genius of the artist and an inspiring team work, with the final resolve of a remarkable work of art! In this case it’s the immersive meditative light sculpture created by the visionary artist @grimanesaamoros which I’m honored to have commissioned for a private collection. 

Titled AETERNUM (‘forever’ in Latin), it’s the artist’s homage to the passage of time and a meditation on eternity. “The term embodies the notion of everlasting existence, perpetual motion, and an eternal flame that never ceases to burn. Central to the artwork is the narrative of the collectors, who see themselves as twin flames whose profound connection is symbolized by an hourglass. Within the hourglass, the sands of time steadily trickle down, representing the inevitable nature of change. Inspired by the moment the hourglass is reset, she breaks the illusion of conclusive endings and embraces the infinite possibilities.” (Artist’s studio)

I’m deeply grateful to you, Grimanesa and your entire talented team, for your creativity, inspiration and being able to put an emotional concept into reality! 🙏❤️ Stay tuned for an interview with the artist where we delve deeper into her inspiration and process.

The Uros Islands, that float on Lake Titicaca, now face depletion, with only approximately 60 islands standing. This work serves as a commentary on the delicate balance between vanishing traditions and the impact of both social dynamics and climate change on Peru’s cultural heritage. Conservation is paramount to preserving the essence of these fleeting islands.

I’ve always cherished the water, captivated by the life it nurtures and the intricate forms it creates. Growing up in coastal Lima has deepened my connection to the ocean. Waterfalls provide an energizing sound, reminiscent of the crashes of waves against rocks from the Pacific. They offer gentle sounds that soothe, creating a serene space for self-reflection and re-centering. Similar to light, water embodies energy, constantly flowing. This piece invites viewers to immerse themselves in an environment that encourages contemplation, embracing the harmonious balance of nature.

The waterfall images were taken by in Luang Prabang, Laos by me as a study ✨
Becoming a wandering nomad and recharging with the desert energy. Mother Nature amazes me.

 ʟᴏᴄᴀᴛɪᴏɴ: ᴄᴜɪᴅᴀᴅ ᴅᴇ ᴍᴇxɪᴄᴏ 📍

In Johannesburg, I learned a lot about the people’s hero, the country’s fighter, and the world’s peacemaker, Nelson Mandela. I ventured to Soweto, a township outside the city where Mandela and his wife Winnie lived before he was incarcerated. It was powerful to be in this place where so much history occurred for the country. I knew of Mandela’s strength, but it was my first time learning about Winnie, another powerful force known as “the mother,” to the cause and fight for freedom. While he was jailed, Winnie herself was thrown in and out of jail, pulled from her children, her movements monitored at all times, and her house was shot at, so much so that she had to build a false wall where the family could hide. History is something we should always remember and never forget. #mandeladay

𝙊𝘾𝙐𝙋𝘼𝙉𝙏𝙀

The Ludwig Museum is a significant historical landmark at the iconic “Deutsche Eck” (German Corner). Within this symbolic space, fragments of the Berlin Wall pay tribute to the “victims of the division,” reminding us of the detrimental consequences of borders on human connections and cultural exchange. OCUPANTE aims to transcend these barriers and forge meaningful connections between individuals and cultures. This sculpture embodies the aspirations of a harmonious and interconnected world where dreams and realities coexist, and cultural exchange thrives. By inviting viewers to enter the museum space, OCUPANTE blurs the line between observer and occupant, encouraging active participation and engagement. It serves as a poignant reminder of the transformative potential when we bridge divides and embrace the richness of diverse perspectives. This lighting sculpture fosters connection. It serves as a living testament to the power of culture, inspiring creativity and nurturing a vibrant global community.

𝙈𝘼𝙍𝙄𝙋𝙊𝙎𝘼 𝘿𝙊𝙍𝘼𝘿𝘼

Inspired by Cuba’s national flower, the Flor de Mariposa, known for transforming form from an elegant blossom to a tool of revolution during colonial times, the installation breathes life into a profound shift in meaning.

The lighting sculpture is a captivating invitation to observe its multidimensional essence from various angles as light perpetually weaves an ever-changing dance of brilliance. MARIPOSA DORADA beckons contemplation of balance. The installation reflects the ever-changing course of history, embodying the spirit of the people and their indomitable will to seek harmony amidst life’s contradictions.

Organic forms and an instinctive approach characterize the work of the award-winning Peruvian-American light artist Grimanesa Amorós. The basis of her fascinating sculptures, however, are the natural sciences, social history, and critical theory.

On the occasion of a 2016 exhibition at the @ludwigmuseumkoblenz, we have published an extensive catalog, which includes an overview of her work. In the concept of her exhibition, the artist led the viewer via the video OCUPANTE finally to a ‘Golden Secret Room”. The volume presents these two works in large-format illustrations and expresses their fluidity and luminosity. Find out more in the link in bio.
